      "url": "https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:ugcPost:7434274813935951872",
      "text": "If you are building in London and need a place to work\n\nCome drop by Unicorn Labs. Free:\n\nIt\u2019s super tough to build something meaningful in your bedroom. A) It\u2019s depressing, and B) you lack the buzz of having like-minded people around.\n\nFergus McKenzie-Wilson and I were literally in the same boat only a few months ago. We were surfing between WeWorks, cafes, and hotel lobbies, without a real HQ. In retrospect, it was super fun but a real productivity killer.\n\nBut honestly, we\u2019re just incredibly thankful. Finding a permanent home in the heart of London Bridge marks a new chapter for everything we\u2019re building.\n\nThe office has already seen new companies created, \u00a3ms in capital raised, and all the other good stuff that you\u2019d want when building from 0 \u2192 1.\n\nOli Kingshott from Halkin Offices really plugged us with some of the best working spaces in London, and while the 60x family is small, the Unicorn Mafia is huge. Our space is now open to the Unicorn Mafia crew.\n\nSo, if you\u2019re a cracked founder/engineer and you're in the area, come visit us!\n\nOur door is always open\u2026 for sponsorship too!\n\nKnow any engineers who should come visit? Tag them below.",
